            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing API Calls for Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batch requests where possible to reduce latency. Use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stream",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter for real-time responses in interactive applications. Cache frequent queries to minimize API calls and costs. For high-throughput scenarios, consider asynchronous processing with tools like Celery or AWS Lambda."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Errors and Monitoring"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The API returns standard HTTP status codes. Common errors include 401 for invalid keys, 429 for rate limits, and 500 for server issues. Implement comprehensive logging and alerting for these codes. Use structured logging to track request IDs for debugging. Integrate with monitoring tools like Prometheus or Datadog to visualize API performance and set up alerts for anomalies."
